<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-10-23T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-10-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/423: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-23T19:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                        1926—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 23—9:45
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>507. Department’s 240, October 22nd. In expressing preference for draft
                            formula set forth in my 462, October 8th and 477, October 14th, am I to
                            understand that Department is unwilling to join in draft formula
                            presented in paragraph 2 of my 497, October 20th?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>